<HEADLINE>
DREIFORT SLUMPING WITH OFF-TARGET SLIDER
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MATT McHALE  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ What's wrong with Darren Dreifort?
</P>
<P>
   He has only one victory since June 30. And since allowing one
hit in eight innings to beat Cincinnati 2-0 on July 20, Dreifort
has three losses, a no decision and a 6.00 ERA.
</P>
<P>
   Dreifort, who allowed 11 hits and five runs in five innings
during Tuesday's 8-6 loss to lowly Florida, was not around after
the game. But others were.
</P>
<P>
   Manager Glenn Hoffman is aware this is just Dreifort's first
season as a starter. But Hoffman also needs Dreifort to step up now
that Ramon Martinez, Hideo Nomo and Ismael Valdes are no longer
part of the Dodgers' rotation.
</P>
<P>
   ``He still seems to be throwing the ball well, he just isn't
making good pitches when he needs to,'' Hoffman said.
</P>
<P>
   ``To me the difference is his slider,'' pitching coach Charlie
Hough said. ``His command is good, but he just isn't throwing the
slider for strikes. It is something we can work on.''
</P>
<P>
   Dreifort has been durable, with a string of 16 starts with six
or more innings. He struck out eight and walked one Tuesday. His
144 strikeouts are seventh in the National League.
</P>
<P>
   __ What a ninth: Matt Mantei opened the inning for the Marlins
and actually retired the first batter, Gary Sheffield. Then he
walked Eric Karros and Bobby Bonilla and allowed a single to Adrian
Beltre to load the bases. He then walked Charles Johnson to score
Karros, but that only made it 8-2.
</P>
<P>
   Marlins manager Jim Leyland turned to Antonio Alfonseca, who
walked pinch-hitter Matt Luke and Eric Young to make it 8-4. Mark
Grudzielanek fell behind 0-2 but singled to center, scoring
Johnson. Raul Mondesi hit a grounder to short, but Edgar Renteria
had no chance for a double play. He rushed the ball and almost
didn't get Mondesi. Luke scored.
</P>
<P>
   ``Our pitchers just weren't prepared,'' said Leyland, who had
Robb Nen in his bullpen last year. ``When these guys aren't in save
situations, they don't prepare.''
</P>
<P>
   The Dodgers had the tying run at second with Sheffield at the
plate. Leyland intentionally walked his former cleanup hitter to
put the winning run on base with Karros at the plate. Karros fell
behind 1-2 and lined to center to end the game.
</P>
<P>
   ``That wasn't disrespect to Karros, it was the ultimate respect
for Sheffield,'' Leyland said. ``Karros has beaten me in a lot of
games. I didn't feel too good doing it, but fortunately it all
worked out.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Quick hits: As expected, National League president Leonard
Coleman denied the New York Mets protest of their July 31 game with
the Dodgers. The Mets claimed Eric Young had not been activated
from the DL in time for the game.... Bobby Bonilla said there was
no added emotion facing the team he helped lead to a World Series
title last season. ``I was only there one year,'' he said. ``I feel
bad for (Leyland). He never got to enjoy the chance to repeat.''...
If you want to say it's not all Dreifort's fault, the Dodgers
haven't scored over 102/3 innings in his past two starts, although
102/3 innings in two starts might be a bigger problem....
Grudzielanek went 3 for 5 and is batting .412 in his past four
games.... Johnson had two passed balls, giving him five for the
year. He had one last season and has 15 in his five-year career.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
