   MULAN-HAIR _ Inspired by the spirited heroines of two new
made-for-little-girls movies, some youngsters are taking up
scissors and trying their hands at shearing their own locks. Snip.
``Look, Mom, I'm Mulan.'' (Gandara, Austin American-Statesman)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   FLA-CROQUET _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ The wicket and mallet set
is hoping a city park in a mixed-income neighborhood will join the
ranks of Mar-a-Lago and The Breakers. ``We have seen the benefits
Tiger Woods has brought to golf. We want the next Tiger Woods to be
a croquet player,'' John Curington wrote in a letter to city
commissioners. (Bierman, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   FAMILY-REUNION _ The Walker family reunion boasted 310 members.
Last weekend, the whole three-day, $10,000 deal included a banquet
at the Marriott, hospitality suite, fashion show with the kids,
all-day picnic and Sunday service. The reunion T-shirts alone were
$600. (Anna, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MINOR-COLUMN _ COLUMBIANA, Ohio _ Let me tell you about this
town. It is small _ 6,000 people. It has the most wonderful park,
the most wonderful old cinema, the most wonderful fall street fair.
For $100,000, you could buy yourself the prettiest house on the
nicest part of Elm Street. (Minor, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MCCARTY-COLUMN _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Looking for light fare, we
headed to the drive-in for ``Parent Trap.'' It was all fun and
froth, exactly what we'd been looking for. Of course, we had to
suspend our disbelief and not ask the obvious questions: Who but a
pair of sociopaths would do this to their kids? How could they be
so attractive and likable? (McCarty, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
