<P>
   NETHAWAY-COLUMN _ The sight of an American flag being torched in
anger outside my Mexico City hotel was startling. Now, 39 years
later, I am not so startled when I encounter anti-Americanism. I am
still not sure, however, why America, which has never taken over
one square-inch of anyone's land, is so despised by so many of the
world's discontents. (Nethaway, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
