<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ROCK-NAMES13-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Choosing a band name? Not now, I'm naked
 &HT;    By Bryon Rivers
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Barenaked Ladies. Cowboy Mouth. Agents of Good Roots.
</P>
<P>
   Some of the bands playing on the H.O.R.D.E. tour have silly
names. But choosing a name for your rock band can be serious
business.
</P>
<P>
   It can be derived from your sound (Metallica), say something
about where you dwell (House of Love, House of Pain) or describe
both your personality and nationality in one shot (Angry Samoans).
</P>
<P>
   If rock bands have shown us anything, it's that anything goes.
Just check out these monikers:
</P>
<P>
   Bands with a God complex: Dashboard Saviors, Jesus Jones,
Screaming Blue Messiahs, God Lives Underwater, The Super-Jesus,
Jesus Lizard, The Jesus and Mary Chain, The Godz, MC 900 FT Jesus
</P>
<P>
   Silly bands: Gee That's A Large Beetle I Wonder If It's
Poisonous, The Bourbon Tabernacle Choir, The Morbid Tavern Apple
Choir, Lee Press-On and The Nails, Screeching Weasel, New Squids on
the Dock, Not Now I'm Naked, Dukes of Hazardous Material, Me First
and the Gimmee Gimmees.
</P>
<P>
   Demented bands: Hamster Sandwich, A Cat Born In an Oven Isn't
Cake, Goldfish Don't Bounce, Grandpa's Become a Fungus, Norman
Bates and the Shower Heads, Amish Rake Fight.
</P>
<P>
   Body Parts bands: Armpit, The Bad Livers, Flaming Lips, Mother
Hips, Belly.
</P>
<P>
   Food bands: Cap'n Crunch and the Cereal Killers, Banana Blender
Surprise, A Box of Fish with Tartar Sauce, Jimmy's Chicken Shack,
Free Beer, Individual Fruit Pie, Jif and the Choosy Mothers, Rage
Against the Coffee Machine.
</P>
<P>
   Self-deprecating bands: Above Average Weight Band, Bad Examples,
Cheepskates, A Confederacy of Dunces, Dopes, Failure, The Germs.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
