seller and publisher Lawrence Ferlinghetti has been named San
Francisco's first poet laureate by Mayor Brown. By GREGORY LEWIS.
</P>
<P>
   SA-SYMPHONY (San Antonio) _ Just a month from opening night, the
San Antonio Symphony's 60th season is threatened by a game of
brinksmanship between its governing board and musicians. By MIKE
GREENBERG.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   OLY-PENTATHLETE (San Antonio) _ Vaho Iagorachvili remembers the
days he lived like a king. As one of the Soviet Union's top 10
athletes, he had the money, the fame and most importantly, he had
the respect. But after some tough years after the breakup of the
Soviet Union, the pentathlete is now coaching in the United States.
By GAGE HARTER.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-49ERS (Stockton, Calif.) _ It didn't matter to the 30,000
cheering fans who showed up that they were paying good money to see
a mere football practice. What was important was that this involved
the 49ers, the team all of Stockton has been nuts over since it
opened its first training camp here 21 days ago. By JOHN
CRUMPACKER.
