<P>
   GLOBAL-WARMING (Washington) _ You'd think people enduring frigid
weather most of the year would welcome a little global warming. But
not Alaskan natives in villages by the Bering and Chukchi Seas, who
say that higher temperatures are making it harder for them to hunt
and fish. Their complaints are recorded in a new report issued by
the environmental activist group Greenpeace. By NICOLE TSONG.
</P>
<P>
   BUSINESS-FINANCIAL NEWS (``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   NEWSPAPERS-ADVERTISING (Vienna, Va.) _ The Newspaper Association
of America (NAA) announces plans for a Newspaper Industry
Communications Center (NICC) that will act as a clearinghouse for
advertisers, ad agencies and newspapers. NAA says the goal is to
simplify the planning, placement and execution of newspaper
advertising by serving as a central communications source. By The
Hearst Newspapers.
</P>
