<P>
   GLOBAL-WARMING (Washington) _ You would think people enduring
frigid weather most of the year would welcome a little global
warming. But not Alaskan natives in villages by the Bering and
Chukchi Seas, who say that higher temperatures are making it harder
for them to hunt and fish. Their complaints are recorded in a new
report issued by the environmental activist group Greenpeace. By
NICOLE TSONG.
