A0424 &Cx1f; tad-z
u e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-TV-WEEKEND-COX     08-12 0488
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TV-WEEKEND-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    This Weekend on TV
 &HT;    By Lyle V. Harris and Bob Longino
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   FRIDAY
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Ulee's Gold'' (1997) 8 p.m. EDT on Cinemax _ Peter Fonda
makes an Oscar-nominated career comeback in this subtle drama about
a Florida beekeeper whose dysfunctional family includes a jailbird
son and a doped-out daughter-in-law. Also stars Patricia Richardson
(``Home Improvement'') as a neighbor who tries to help. 120m.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Frank Sinatra: The Very Good Years'' PBS (check local
listings)_ The Chairman of the Board sings his greatest hits in
this ``Great Performances'' retrospective from the 13 TV specials
Sinatra appeared in during the 1960s and '70s. Among the crooner's
legendary songs featured here are ``My Way,'' ``I've Got You Under
My Skin'' and ``Come Fly With Me.''
</P>
<P>
   -- ``The Usual Suspects'' (1995) 9 p.m. EDT on USA _ Hip, dark,
twisty whodunit with Gabriel Byrne, Kevin Spacey and Benicio Del
Toro as career crooks who get hoodwinked by a shadowy master
criminal named Keyser Soze. This meaty, old-fashioned film noir (it
won Academy Awards for best screenplay and for Spacey for
supporting actor) will keep you guessing until the final frame.
Also airs at 7 p.m. Saturday (515689). 130m.
</P>
<P>
   SATURDAY
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Saturday Night Fever'' (1977) 1:30 p.m. EDT on TBS _
Leather jackets, skin-tight gabardine pants, platform shoes and the
Funky Chicken? Disco never dies in this star-making,
decade-defining drama starring John Travolta as a not-so-bright kid
from Brooklyn on the fast track to nowhere who dons a white suit
and struts his stuff on the dance floor. And please, don't touch
the hair. Anything but the hair. Also airs at 8 p.m. EDT on TNT.
145m.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Ku Klux Klan: A Secret History'' 4 p.m. EDT on the History
Channel _ Find out more about America's oldest home-grown hate
group, from their secret rituals to the hoods and burning crosses
that remain potent symbols of their pursuit of white supremacy.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``2 Days in the Valley'' (1996) 8 p.m. EDT on Cinemax _ Danny
Aiello stars as a bumbling crook with a bad toupee who falls for
the assistant to a snotty Los Angeles artist in this quirky comedic
drama. Look for the always eerie James Spader as Aiello's
double-crossing partner and Charleze Theron in one of the best cat
fights ever filmed. 120m.
</P>
<P>
   SUNDAY
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Sports of the 20th Century: Babe Ruth'' 8 p.m. EDT on HBO _
Long before there was a Mark McGwire or a Sammy Sosa, the slugger
they called the Bambino ruled the New York Yankees, baseball and
the world. Clips show more than a few of his mammoth home runs.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``The Practice'' 10 p.m. EDT on ABC _ Interest in David E.
Kelley's interesting drama is picking up. The series, nominated
this year for a best drama Emmy, moves to Sunday nights, its new
home for the coming fall season.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
