<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FOOD-RECIPESWAP13-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Salad suited for light meals or grilled meats
 &HT;    By Marcia Langhenry
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Connie McGrath of Atlanta responded to Marilynn Hinton's request
for a Greek salad with dressing with this one she's been making for
a long time. Originally called Peasant Salad, it stands alone as a
light meal or pairs well with grilled meats.
</P>
<P>
   These days, McGrath makes a lighter version by halving the oil
and vinegar, while using the same amounts of mint, garlic and
oregano. Either way, she says, it's good.
</P>
<P>
   Here's the original version.
</P>
<P>
   SALAD
</P>
<P>
   Greek Salad With Dressing
</P>
<P>
   Makes 6 servings
</P>
<P>
   Preparation time: 20 minutes
</P>
<P>
   1large head romaine lettuce, washed and chilled
</P>
<P>
   2medium tomatoes,
</P>
<P>
   cut into 1/2-inch wedges
</P>
<P>
   1large cucumber, peeled and thinly sliced
</P>
<P>
   8radishes, trimmed and thinly sliced
</P>
<P>
   6green onions, cut into
</P>
<P>
   1/4-inch slices
</P>
<P>
   6ounces feta cheese,
</P>
<P>
   crumbled
</P>
<P>
   12kalamata olives
</P>
<P>
   1teaspoon finely chopped fresh mint or 1/4 teaspoon dried mint
</P>
<P>
   1/2cup olive oil
</P>
<P>
   3tablespoons fresh
</P>
<P>
   lemon juice
</P>
<P>
   2tablespoons red wine
</P>
<P>
   vinegar
</P>
<P>
   1garlic clove, crushed
</P>
<P>
   1teaspoon finely chopped fresh oregano or
</P>
<P>
   1/4 teaspoon dried
</P>
<P>
   Tear lettuce into bite-size pieces. Place in large salad bowl.
Add tomatoes, cucumber, radishes, green onions, cheese and olives.
Sprinkle with mint. In a small bowl, whisk oil, lemon juice,
vinegar, garlic and oregano. Pour over salad; toss lightly until
thoroughly mixed. Serve immediately.
</P>
<P>
   Per serving: 276 calories, 5 grams protein, 26 grams fat
(percent calories from fat, 84), 8 grams carbohydrates, 25
milligrams cholesterol, 404 milligrams sodium.
</P>
<P>
   Requests
</P>
<P>
   -- W. Bradley of Milledgeville is hoping someone has a recipe
for cottage cheese soup that was flavored with garlic.
</P>
<P>
   -- Betty Mullins of Lawrenceville is searching for a recipe for
Pina Colada Cake.
</P>
<P>
   -- Judy Carpenter of Gainesville hopes to find the instructions
for Coconut Custard Pie with filling prepared in the microwave.
</P>
<P>
   Where to write
</P>
<P>
   Recipes or requests should be sent to Recipe Swap, Food
Department, Cox News Service, P.O. Box 4689, Atlanta, GA 30302.
Include a daytime telephone number. E-mail: mlanghenry(at)ajc.com.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
