<SLUG> BC-KIDS'-BOOKS-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SUMMER READING FOR KIDS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SANDY GUERRA-CLINE 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``The Legend of Sleeping Bear''
</P>
<P>
   Author: Kathy-jo Wargin
</P>
<P>
   Publisher: Sleeping Bear Press
</P>
<P>
   Cost: $16.96
</P>
<P>
   Ages: All
</P>
<P>
   If you are the kind of parent who weeps at Kodak moments, ``The
Legend of Sleeping Bear'' will bring more than a tear to your eye.
The people who normally tease you will probably be moved, too.
</P>
<P>
   ``Legend'' is a gentle retelling of the Indian legend of the
great mother bear who sleeps on the shores of Lake Michigan. Driven
by a forest fire to swim across the lake with her two small cubs,
the mother bear exhorts her children to keep swimming. They swim
all day, the mother constantly looking back to check on the cubs'
progress. Night falls, and still she looks for them. When the sun
rises, her cubs are gone.
</P>
<P>
   The mother bear reaches the shore, where she begins pacing up
and down at the water's edge. ``My children, can you hear me? I
will wait for you forever,'' she shouts into the wind.
</P>
<P>
   And she does. The seasons come and go, but the mother bear will
not be moved. After a time, the ``great spirit of the land'' sees
her devotion and rewards it in a most marvelous way.
</P>
<P>
   The way this book rewards you _ in a most marvelous way.
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
