<P>
   &UR; BILL'S WORLD &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; By Bill Tammeus, The Kansas City Star &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Mr. Clinton is on the road for part of this week. No, it's
mostly a political trip, not Starr-approved work-release.
</P>
<P>
   Some members of Congress want Ken Starr to file an impeachment
report so the matter can be settled quickly. Well, plus they want
to read about Monica's dress.
</P>
<P>
   ``There is no way out if we start running away from this kind of
conduct,'' Mr. Clinton said this week. No, he was talking about
fighting terrorism, not Starrorism.
</P>
<P>
   Aunt Ilse from Oelwein says if Starr submits an impeachment
report to Congress it will get much higher readership if it
includes pictures.
</P>
<P>
   Mr. Clinton's grand jury testimony will be via closed-circuit
TV. That's probably how he should spend any future time with White
House interns.
</P>
<P>
   A New York publisher says Monica Lewinsky treated her stained
dress like a trophy. Apparently journalists aren't the only ones
who value leaks.
</P>
<P>
   The president calls acts of terrorism ``inhuman.'' Don't we all
wish.
</P>
<P>
   Newly released government statistics show July was the hottest
month on record. Bet Mr. Clinton would cast his vote for this
month.
</P>
<P>
   Unless we act, says Al Gore, ``we can expect even more extreme
weather _ more heat waves, more flooding, more powerful storms and
more drought.'' Plus, of course, the usual run of bad movies about
all that.
</P>
<P>
   ``You don't have to be a scientist to know it's been hot this
summer,'' Gore says. In fact, you can be way below a scientist.
Like vice president.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
