   LONG-DISTANCE-DEGREE _ Southwest Texas State recently got a
federal grant to set up a Master's degree program in Applied
Geography. The special part is, students get their education long-
distance using technology and innovation to bridge the distance.
The biggest winners? Teachers in the valley who do not have access
to such programs. (Rodriguez, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   SMALLBIZ-RETIREMENT _ In today's tight job market, more and more
small businesses are offering retirement plans as an incentive to
attract good workers and compete with bigger employers. But picking
the right type of plan depends on the size of the company, how much
it can spend on plan administration and how much it might grow.
(Tyson, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
