<SLUG> BC-EMBASSIES-RISK-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NO MORE `GARDEN SPOTS' AMONG US EMBASSIES 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (w and i coding)   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By DAVID L. MARCUS   AND ESTELLA DURAN  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ When bombs ripped apart two US embassies last week,
the losses were not limited to people and property. A way of life
disappeared, too.
</P>
<P>
   The diplomats, secretaries and accountants who work at America's
288 embassies and consulates around the world have long divided
