this summer? Institutional investors, the same powerful group that
sold aggressively in October, when the Dow tumbled 554 points, or
7.2 percent, in a single day. And the same big-time players who
have soured repeatedly on the bull market, only to jump back in
later, after smaller investors have quietly affirmed their faith.
By David Barboza.
