runs in his last 38 innings for a 1.18 ERA. He lost to the Padres
3-2 on May 8, giving up three runs on six hits; opposing pitcher
Andy Ashby allowed nine hits and won. Glavine has won 10 times at
Qualcomm in 16 career starts. He will be careful facing
