(.322 with two home runs). No one on the current Braves roster was
around the last time Langston faced Atlanta, which is probably a
good thing. In his only career start against the Braves, he threw a
shutout in 1989 when he pitched for Montreal. His return to the
National League has not been a smooth one. He spent more than four
weeks on the disabled list (April 15-May 23) with a strained
shoulder and has had little luck since the All-Star break. He is
1-3 in five second-half starts, having given up 23 runs and 37 hits
in his last 20 2/3 innings. He has not pitched past the sixth
inning in six-straight games and only twice in 14 starts this year.
</P>
