was destroyed in a terrorist bombing on Friday that injured her and
took the lives of three dozen American and Kenyan colleagues. She
has had to re-establish her mission while overseeing a chaotic
rescue operation. To make matters harder, she has also become the
focus of anger among many Kenyans. BY James C. McKinley Jr. 1,300
words.
