<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-USANETWORKS-CITYSEARCH-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
USA NETWORKS SAID TO PLAN CITYSEARCH DEAL 
</HEADLINE>
   (bl)  
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   USA Networks Inc. is expected to merge its Ticketmaster Online
service with Citysearch, an Internet company that produces local
guides of events, according to a person close to USA Networks.
</P>
<P>
   USA Networks already owns a 13 percent stake in Citysearch, for
which it paid $20 million a year ago, a person with knowledge of
the original negotiation said.
</P>
<P>
   After the merger, USA will own 62.5 percent of the merged
company and Citysearch will own the rest. Citysearch, which had
planned a public offering this week, lost $37 million last year on
revenue of $6 million, according to a USA Networks executive.
</P>
<P>
   Ticketmaster Online was started in 1994, receives four million
visits a month and sold about 10 million tickets in July, said Alan
Citron, who has been running the multimedia operation of USA
Networks. USA Networks chairman Barry Diller has been a proponent
of local programming and information services.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
