<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-12 22:06 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A1104 &Cx1f; taf-z
u w &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-CLINTON-DEFENSE-TEXT-     08-12 0608
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CLINTON-DEFENSE-TEXT-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TEXT OF SOLICITATION LETTER FOR LEGAL EXPENSE TRUST 
</HEADLINE>
   (sidebar with CLINTON-DEFENSE-FUND)  
 (bl)  
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ Following is the solicitation letter sent to
supporters of the President and Mrs. Clinton under the signature of
former Sen. David Pryor, D- Ark., as provided by the Clinton Legal
Expense Trust. Those receiving the letter also get a certificate
for donors to sign and return with their checks.
</P>
<P>
   LETTER
</P>
<P>
   In today's political climate, public service can exact a
disturbing price. There is perhaps no better example than the
financial crisis now facing President and Mrs. Clinton.
</P>
<P>
   News reports reflect that to conduct his four-year investigation
of the Clintons, the independent counsel already has spent more
than $40 million of taxpayer money. And supporters of Paula Jones
continue to fund her case on appeal.
</P>
<P>
   Since entering the White House, President and Mrs. Clinton have
accumulated almost $5 million in legal expenses _ an amount far
beyond the President's total compensation or the first family's net
worth. They are personally liable for these bills.
</P>
<P>
   The Clinton Legal Expense Trust has been established to enable
supporters of the first family throughout America to help defray
these enormous costs. Because you are a supporter of the President,
we are writing to ask for your help.
</P>
<P>
   Contributions to the trust can be made by any United States
citizen who is not a lobbyist or an employee of the executive
branch of the Federal Government. Contributions from PAC's,
corporations or labor organizations are not permitted, and no
individual can contribute more than $10,000 per year.
</P>
<P>
   All of us should be concerned when the financial burden of
public service becomes so great as to discourage good men and women
from seeking office. Our President deserves the chance to do his
job and serve our nation unburdened by the prospect of a huge
personal debt.
</P>
<P>
   Few Americans would deny that President and Mrs. Clinton have
worked tirelessly for the benefit of our nation. Their work has
helped produce economic prosperity, lower crime and most
importantly a new optimism about America and our future.
</P>
<P>
   Their dedication and their achievement deserve our thanks and
our generosity.
</P>
<P>
   I have known the President for more than 30 years, and I'm sure
that your help will be deeply appreciated by the first family.
Please join other friends of the Clintons in contributing to the
trust. Your contribution will make a big difference.
</P>
<P>
   P.S.: If you are disturbed by the way politics is conducted
today, then what better response than to make your own gesture of
decency and generosity. I know that it will be enormous comfort to
the first family to know that so many Americans appreciate their
work and have come to their aid. Thank you so much for any
contribution you send.
</P>
<P>
   CERTIFICATE
</P>
<P>
   Enclosed with the mailer is
</P>
<P>
   To the trustees: In connection to my contribution to the Clinton
Legal Expense Trust, I hereby certify that:
</P>
<P>
   _ I'm a citizen of the United States;
</P>
<P>
   _ I've made my contribution voluntarily and with my own personal
funds;
</P>
<P>
   _ I'm not a lobbyist registered with the Federal Government;
</P>
<P>
   _ I'm not employed by the executive branch of the United States
Government;
</P>
<P>
   _ Including this contribution, I've not contributed more than
$10,000 this calendar year to the Clinton Legal Expense Trust;
</P>
<P>
   _ I understand that my name, city, state and the amount of my
contribution will be publicly disclosed;
</P>
<P>
   _ I understand that my contribution is not tax-deductible.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
