<SLUG> BC-FBN-JETS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TESTAVERDE COULD START FOR JETS AGAINST BALTIMORE 
</HEADLINE>
  (mk) 
 By FRANK LITSKY   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   HEMPSTEAD, N.Y. _ The Jets' putative quarterback controversy
continued brewing Wednesday with the belief that 37-year-old Vinny
Testaverde, acquired in the off-season ostensibly as a backup, will
very likely start against his former team, the Baltimore Ravens,
Saturday night at Giants Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   When training camp began, coach Bill Parcells indicated that
Glenn Foley, a fifth-year pro, would replace Neil O'Donnell as the
starter. Foley was decent if not spectacular as the starter in last
Thursday night's 29-15 victory over the Philadelphia Eagles.
</P>
<P>
   On Tuesday, Parcells said there was ``a pretty good chance'' he
would start Testaverde in the second preseason game. Before
Wednesday afternoon's practice, Parcells discussed his quarterback
plans with his coaches, but not with the quarterbacks, and he would
not disclose his decision. The starting quarterback usually takes
the most snaps in practice, but Wednesday afternoon Foley and
Testaverde split the work evenly.
</P>
<P>
   ``Nothing has changed,'' Parcells said when asked whether
Testaverde has closed the gap on Foley. ``I'm not trying to be a
jerk. I'm not doing it to stir the pot. I look at different things
with different people.''
</P>
<P>
   As if to illustrate his point, Parcells said this week's
starters would probably include Marcus Coleman instead of Otis
Smith at cornerback, Jerald Sowell instead of Keith Byars at
fullback and a healthier Curtis Martin instead of Richie Anderson
at tailback. But quarterback is the position that attracts the most
attention on most teams, and the Jets' first two quarterbacks are
talking party line. They are saying nothing incendiary, nothing
even remotely argumentative.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm confident in my ability to play quarterback, for this or
any team,'' Testaverde said. ``I tell myself I'm not going to try
to figure coach Parcells out. He may want to start me because we're
playing my old team, or it could be a hundred other reasons. I
don't look at it too much. I prepare myself as if I'm the starter.
It's a long season. A lot of people get to play.''
</P>
<P>
   And Foley said: ``I never looked at it as my job. I looked at it
as an open competition, and I'm for that. I have to understand that
everything I do, everything on the practice field, I have to be
perfect. There's always been controversy and competition. I don't
think it's that big an issue. If I do well, I should play. If I
don't, Vinny should play.''
</P>
<P>
   When Parcells was coaching the Giants, he had quarterback
controversies involving Phil Simms and Jeff Hostetler, both of whom
would win Super Bowls for him. He made light of the situation here.
</P>
<P>
   ``I already think I know what I'm going to do,'' he said. ``It's
just a question of how we're going to do it.''
</P>
<P>
   A likely option is to start Testaverde on Saturday, follow him
with last year's third-stringer, Chuck Clements, and finish with
Foley. That would allow Parcells to see Testaverde with the first
offensive line and possibly allow Foley to run a game-ending
two-minute drill, something the coach also wants to see.
</P>
<P>
   But questions remain. Is Parcells dissatisfied with Foley so
far? Is he trying to egg Foley on? Can Testaverde wrestle away the
starting job? Parcells did not say.
</P>
<P>
   ``At the beginning of camp,'' Parcells said, ``I said Glenn is
going to get the benefit of the doubt. If it's obvious Vinny is
playing better, I've got to go by what I see, not just at
quarterback, but at any position, just not this year, but any
year.''
</P>
<P>
   The answer of who will start at quarterback Saturday may not be
known until Friday's walk-through practice. No one seemed overly
concerned. When Keyshawn Johnson, the wide receiver, was asked if
the team was talking about the quarterback situation, he shook his
head.
</P>
<P>
   ``Nobody is talking about it,'' he told reporters. ``Just you.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
