grant them a religious divorce. The court grants the women
annulments instead. But without a religious divorce, a woman is in
limbo: she cannot remarry within Orthodoxy, and should she do so
elsewhere, any children she may bear will be considered
illegitimate and themselves barred from marrying Orthodox Jews. But
men without religious divorces face no such consequences. By Nadine
Brozan.
