</HEADLINE>
 
 This ``separate buy'' article is from Latin Trade magazine,
America's leading journal of Latin American business, finance and
trade: &HT;    GOOD TIMES GONE. Discovery by U.S. authorities of a parasite
called cyclospora traced to Guatemalan raspberry growers left
business in a shambles. Now, U.S. lawmakers are investigating
quality control of all food imports.
 &HT;    Moved as BC-LATIN-GROWERS-BEWARE-LATINTRADE-NYTSF in ``i''
international and ``f'' financial files.
